  1. Choose number of the cluster centre and no. of clusters
normalize <- function(x){
  return ((x-min(x))/(max(x)-min(x)))
}

data$RedMeat <- normalize(data$RedMeat)
data$WhiteMeat <- normalize(data$WhiteMeat)
data$Eggs <- normalize(data$Eggs)
data$Milk <- normalize(data$Milk)
data$Fish <- normalize(data$Fish)
data$Cereals <- normalize(data$Cereals)
data$Starch <- normalize(data$Starch)
data$Nuts <- normalize(data$Nuts)
data$Fr.Veg <- normalize(data$Fr.Veg)


result <- kmeans(data, 3)
result$centers

2 a) To display Cluster : use plot()

result$cluster <- as.factor(result$cluster)
plot(data, col=result$cluster)

2 b) To display cluster centre : library(factoextra) , function : fviz_cluster()

library(factoextra)

2 c) To display cluster : use Clustergram(), autoplot()

library(shipunov)

Clustergram(data)

library(ggfortify)
autoplot(stats::kmeans(data, 3), data = data)

2 e) 1. Elbow method

library(NbClust)

fviz_nbclust(data, kmeans, method = "wss") + geom_vline(xintercept = 4, linetype = 2) + labs(subtitle = "Elbow method")

2 e) 2. Silhouette method

fviz_nbclust(data, kmeans, method = "silhouette") + labs(subtitle = "Silhouette method")

2 e) 3. Gap statistic

set.seed(123)
fviz_nbclust(data, kmeans, nstart = 25,  method = "gap_stat", nboot = 50) + labs(subtitle = "Gap statistic method")
